Britain's Prince William on Thursday launched the "most prestigious" environmental prize of all time, aimed at turning "pessimism into optimism" by rewarding innovative solutions to the planet's biggest problems.The Earthshot Prize will present five £1 million ($1.3 million) awards each year for the next 10 years, to "incentivise change and help to repair our planet over the next ten years," said his office in London.AFP 
